body:
The following example fails:

``` SystemVerilog
module t;
    function void myfunc();
    endfunction : myfunc

    class Cls #(int A = 0);
        function new();
        endfunction : new

        function void myfunc();
        endfunction : myfunc
    endclass

    Cls #(100) cls;

    // this block is following the definition of Cls
    initial begin
        cls = new; // Internal Error: Broken link in node 
        myfunc();  // Internal Error: Broken link in node 
    end
endmodule
```

It also causes segmentation fault if `--debug-check` is off.

`V3LinkDot::linkDotPrimary` mistakenly link the two nodes (the 'new' and the 'myfunc' in the initial block) using the symbol table for class Cls, and it's because LinkDotResolveVisitor didn't restore the symbol table (m_ds.m_dotSymp) before finishing visiting AstClass nodes, so this can be simply fixed by restoring the variable before exiting the `visit(AstClass*)` function.

I added a VL_GET_SAVED macro to access variables saved by VL_RESTORER. It seems to be simpler but I'm not sure if it's a good idea (perhaps it can also be used in other places?).
